in 1983, and received the Grand Cross of the Court of Honour in 1991.<ref name=\"masons\">{{cite web| url=http://scottishrite.org/2011/04/dedication-of-long-beach-scottish-rite-theatre-to-actor-brother-ernest-borgnine| title=Dedication of Long Beach Scottish Rite Theatre to Actor & Brother Ernest Borgnine| publisher=Scottishrite.org| date=7 May 2011| accessdate=2012-11-08| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120510063626/http://scottishrite.org/2011/04/dedication-of-long-beach-scottish-rite-theatre-to-actor-brother-ernest-borgnine/| archive-date=May 10, 2012| url-status=dead}}</ref> He was also a member of the Loyal Order of Moose at that organization's Lodge in [[Junction City, Oregon]]. He volunteered to be [[Stories of Service]] National spokesman, urging his fellow World War II vets to come forward and share their stories.\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" width=\"100%\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 1951 || ''[[China Corsair]]'' || Hu Chang ||\n|-\n| ''[[The Whistle at Eaton Falls]]'' || Bill Street ||\n|-\n| ''[[The Mob (film)|The Mob]]'' || Joe Castro ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 1953 || ''[[Treasure of the Golden Condor]]'' || Bit part ||\n|-\n| ''[[The Stranger Wore a Gun]]'' || Bull Slager ||\n|-\n| ''[[From Here to Eternity]]'' || Staff Sergeant James R. \"Fatso\" Judson ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" | 1954 || ''[[Johnny Guitar]]'' || Bart Lonergan ||\n|-\n| ''[[Demetrius and the Gladiators]]'' || Strabo ||\n|-\n| ''{{sortname|The|Bounty Hunter|dab=1954 film}}'' || Bill Rachin ||\n|-\n| ''[[Vera Cruz (film)|Vera Cruz]]'' || Donnegan ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\" | 1955 || ''[[Bad Day at Black Rock]]'' || Coley Trimble ||\n|-\n| ''[[Violent Saturday]]'' || Stadt, Amish Farmer ||\n|-\n| ''[[Marty (film)|Marty]]'' || Marty Piletti || [[Academy Award for Best Actor]]<br />[[BAFTA Award for Best Actor in a Leading Role|BAFTA Award for Best Foreign Actor]]<br />[[Golden Globe Award for Best Actor \u2013 Motion Picture Dr