emy Mind'' || Command || Voice\n|-\n| ''{{sortname|The|Genesis Code}}'' || Carl Taylor ||\n|-\n| ''[[Red (2010 film)|Red]]'' || Henry / Recordskeeper ||\n|-\n| ''[[Another Harvest Moon]]'' || Frank ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" | 2011 || ''[[Night Club (2011 film)|Night Club]]'' || Albert || Accolade Competition for Leading Actor<br />Frank Currier Actor's Award<br />SINY Film Festival Award for Best Actor\n|-\n| ''{{sortname|The|Lion of Judah}}'' || Slink || Voice\n|-\n| ''[[Love's Christmas Journey]]'' || Nicolas ||\n|-\n| ''[[Snatched (2011 film)|Snatched]]'' || Big Frank Baum ||\n|-\n| 2012 || ''[[The Man Who Shook the Hand of Vicente Fernandez]]'' || Rex Page ||\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" width=\"100%\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 1951 || ''[[Captain Video and His Video Rangers]]'' || Nargola || 3 episodes\n|-\n| ''[[Goodyear Playhouse]]'' || Sgt. Lenahan || Episode: \"The Copper\"\n|-\n| 1951, 1952 || ''[[The Philco Television Playhouse]]'' || Mathew O'Rourke || 2 episodes\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" | 1954 || ''[[The Lone Wolf (TV series)|The Lone Wolf]]'' || Saks || Episode: \"The Avalanche Story (a.k.a. The Reno Story)\"\n|-\n| ''[[The Danny Thomas Show]]'' || Cop || Episode: \"Rusty Runs Away\"\n|-\n| ''[[Ford Theatre]]'' || Gus White || Episode: \"Night Visitor\"\n|-\n| ''Waterfront'' || Jack Bannion || 2 episodes\n|-\n| 1957 || ''[[Navy Log]]'' || Host || Episode: \"Human Bomb\"\n|-\n| 1957\u201361 ||  ''[[Wagon Train]]'' || Willy Moran / Earl Packer / Estaban Zamora || 4 episodes\n|-\n| 1957, 1960 || ''[[Dick Powell's Zane Grey Theatre]]'' || Willie / Big Jim Morrison || 2 episodes\n|-\n| 1959, 1960 || ''[[Laramie (TV series)|Laramie]]'' || Boone Caudie / Major Prescott || 2 episodes\n|-\n| 1961 || ''{{sortname|The|Blue Angels|dab=TV series}}'' || Unknown || Episode: \"The Blue Leaders\"\n|-\n| 1962\u20131966 || ''[[McHale's Navy]]'' || Lieutenant Commander Quinton McHale || Nominated \u2013 [[Primetime Emmy Award fo