{"title_page": "Calocucullia celsiae", "text_new": "{{short description|Species of moth}}\n{{Taxobox\n| name = Calocucullia celsiae\n| image = \n| image_width = 200px\n| image_caption = \n| regnum = [[Animal]]ia\n| phylum = [[Arthropod]]a\n| subphylum = [[Hexapoda]]\n| classis = [[Insect]]a\n| ordo = [[Lepidoptera]]\n| familia = [[Noctuidae]]\n| genus = ''[[Calocucullia]]''\n| species = '''''C. celsiae'''''\n| binomial = ''Calocucullia celsiae''\n| binomial_authority = (Herrich-Sch\u00e4ffer, 1850)\n| synonyms =\n*''Cucullia celsiae'' <small>Herrich-Sch\u00e4ffer, 1850</small>\n}} \n'''''Calocucullia celsiae''''' is a [[moth]] of the family [[Noctuidae]]. It is found from the [[Balkan]]s to [[Turkey]], northern [[Iraq]], [[Armenia]], [[Iran]], [[Israel]], [[Jordan]] and [[Lebanon]].\n\nAdults are on wing from January to April. There is one generation per year.\n\nLarvae have been recorded on ''[[Hesperis desertorum]]'' in Bulgaria.\n\n==Subspecies==\n*''Calocucullia celsiae celsiae''\n*''Calocucullia celsiae levantina'' (Levant)\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.redalyc.org/pdf/455/45512912.pdf Cuculliinae of Israel]\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q5023134}}\n\n[[Category:Cuculliinae]]\n[[Category:Moths of Europe]]\n[[Category:Moths of Asia]]\n\n\n{{Cuculliinae-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Species of moth}}\n{{Taxobox\n| name = Calocucullia celsiae\n| image = \n| image_width = 200px\n| image_caption = \n| regnum = [[Animal]]ia\n| phylum = [[Arthropod]]a\n| subphylum = [[Hexapoda]]\n| classis = [[Insect]]a\n| ordo = [[Lepidoptera]]\n| familia = [[Noctuidae]]\n| genus = ''[[Calocucullia]]''\n| species = '''''C. celsiae'''''\n| binomial = ''Calocucullia celsiae''\n| binomial_authority = (Herrich-Sch\u00e4ffer, 1850)\n| synonyms =\n*''Cucullia celsiae'' <small>Herrich-Sch\u00e4ffer, 1850</small>\n}} \n'''''Calocucullia celsiae''''' is a [[moth]] of the family [[Noctuidae]]. It is found from the [[Balkan]]s to [[Turkey]], northern [[Iraq]], [[Armenia]], [[Iran]], [[Israel]], [[Jordan]] and [[Lebanon]].\n\nAdults are on wing from January to April. There is one generation per year.\n\nLarvae have been recorded on ''[[Hesperis desertorum]]'' in Bulgaria.\n\n==Subspecies==\n*''Calocucullia celsiae celsiae''\n*''Calocucullia celsiae levantina'' (Levant)\n\n==External links==\n*[http://redalyc.uaemex.mx/redalyc/html/455/45512912/45512912.html Cuculliinae of Israel]{{dead link|date=July 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q5023134}}\n\n[[Category:Cuculliinae]]\n[[Category:Moths of Europe]]\n[[Category:Moths of Asia]]\n\n\n{{Cuculliinae-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Logan", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:bad link repair", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Calocucullia_celsiae"}
{"title_page": "Oyo Rooms", "text_new": "{{short description|Indian hospitality company}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name        = Oyo Rooms\n| logo        = OYO Rooms (logo).png\n| logo_size   = \n| type        = [[Privately held company]]\n| trade_name  = OYO Rooms<br>OYO Hotels and Homes\n| industry    = [[Hospitality industry|Hospitality]]\n| founded     = {{start date and age|df=yes|2013}}\n| location    = [[Gurgaon, Haryana]], India\n| founder     = [[Ritesh Agarwal]]\n| key_people  = Ritesh Agarwal (CEO)\n| area_served = [[Asia]], [[Europe]] and [[America]]s\n| website     = {{url|www.oyorooms.com}}\n}}\n[[File:OYO Fenglin Hotel in Changshu.jpg|thumb|OYO in [[Changshu]], [[Jiangsu]], [[China]]]]\n'''Oyo Rooms''' (stylised as '''OYO'''), also known as '''Oyo Homes & Hotels''', is an Indian hotel chain. It is one of the largest and fastest-growing hospitality chain of leased and franchised hotels, homes and living spaces.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ft.com/content/e515c058-5e24-11ea-b0ab-339c2307bcd4|title=Subscribe to read {{!}} Financial Times|website=www.ft.com|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.moneycontrol.com/news/business/oyo-says-it-is-worlds-3rd-largest-hotel-chain-by-room-count-4191531.html|title=With 8.5 lakh rooms, Oyo claims third spot globally|date=10 July 2019|work=[[Moneycontrol.com]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.financialexpress.com/industry/sme/how-oyo-became-indias-3rd-best-company-to-work-for-in-just-6-years/1540659/|title=How OYO became India's 3rd best company to work for in just 6 years|date=7 April 2019|work=[[The Financial Express (India)]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last1=Gooptu|first1=Biswarup|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/startups/newsbuzz/have-become-the-second-largest-hotel-group-in-china-oyo/articleshow/69445392.cms|title=OYO claims to be second-largest hotel group in China|date=22 May 2019|newspaper=[[The Economic Times]]}}</ref> Founded in 2013 by [[Ritesh Agarwal]], OYO initially consisted mainly of budget hotels. The startup expanded globally with thousands of [[hotels]], [[vacation homes]] and millions of rooms in hundreds of cities in India, Malaysia,<ref>{{Cite web | title=OYO Rooms Goes International; Launches in Malaysia | url=https://inc42.com/flash-feed/oyo-rooms-launches-operations-in-malaysia/ | first=Aparna | last=Mishra | work=Inc42 | date=12 January 2016}}</ref> UAE, Nepal,<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/companies/oyo-expands-international-presence-with-hotel-launch-in-nepal-117042700475_1.html | title=OYO expands international presence with hotel launch in Nepal | work=[[Business Standard]] | date=27 April 2017}}</ref> China, Brazil, Mexico, UK, Philippines, Japan,<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/startups/newsbuzz/oyo-commences-hotel-operations-in-japan/articleshow/68716847.cms | title=OYO and SoftBank form JV to launch hotels business in Japan |  work=[[The Economic Times]] | date=4 April 2019}}</ref> Saudi Arabia, Sri Lanka,<ref>{{Cite news | url=http://www.dailymirror.lk/article/OYO-expands-international-presence-entering-Sri-Lanka-159788.html | title=OYO expands international presence entering Sri Lanka |  work=[[Daily Mirror]] | date=14 December 2018}}</ref> Indonesia, Vietnam, the United States<ref>{{Cite web | title=Hotel Unicorn Oyo Plots $300 Million Push into the U.S. Market | url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2019-06-19/hotel-unicorn-oyo-plots-300-million-push-into-the-u-s-market | work=[[Bloomberg L.P]] | date=19 June 2019}}</ref> and more.<ref>{{Cite web | title=More room at the top | url=https://www.fortuneindia.com/venture/more-room-at-the-top/101637 | first=DEEPTI | last=CHAUDHARY | work=[[Fortune (magazine)|Fortune]] | date=2 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.ndtv.com/people/at-21-hes-the-mind-behind-multi-million-dollar-start-up-oyo-1204353 | title=At 21, He's the Mind Behind Multi-Million Dollar Start-Up OYO | first=Natasha | last=Jog | work=[[NDTV]] | date=6 August 2015}}</ref> \n\nThe company's investors include [[SoftBank Group]], Greenoaks Capital, Sequoia India, Lightspeed India, Hero Enterprise, [[Airbnb]] and [[China Lodging Group]].\n\n==History==\nIn 2012, Ritesh Agarwal launched Oravel Stays to enable listing and booking of budget accommodations. After undertaking months of research and staying in various [[bed and breakfast]] homes, [[guest house]]s, and small hotels across India, he pivoted Oravel to OYO in 2013.<ref>{{Cite news | url=http://www.forbesindia.com/article/8th-anniversary-special/how-oyos-ritesh-agarwal-transformed-the-business-of-budget-accommodation/46971/1 | title=How OYO's Ritesh Agarwal transformed the business of budget accommodation | first=PARAMITA | last=CHATTERJEE | work=[[Forbes]] | date=16 May 2017}}</ref>\n\nOYO partners with hotels to give similar guest experience across cities.and [https://couponmandi.com/in/oyo-rooms-coupons-promo-code-deals-offers/ Oyo offers] affordable and better quality room service almost everywhere.  Shortly after launching Oravel Stays, Ritesh Agarwal received a grant of [[United States dollar|$]]100,000 as part of the [[Thiel Fellowship]] from [[Peter Thiel]].<ref>{{Cite news | title=Oravel founder Ritesh Agarwal wins Thiel Fellowship | url=https://www.livemint.com/Companies/ZbqDGYUN0yfhtB2syOIDVP/Oravel-founder-Ritesh-Agarwal-wins-Thiel-Fellowship.html | work=[[Mint (newspaper)|Mint]] | date=10 May 2013}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.businessinsider.com/ritesh-agarwal-interview-with-founder-of-peter-thiel-backed-oyo-2018-9 | title=Ritesh Agarwal: Interview with founder of Peter Thiel-backed Oyo | first=Shona | last=Ghosh | work=[[Business Insider]] | date=22 September 2018 | url-access=subscription}}</ref> OYO currently has over 17,000 employees globally,<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/companies/oyo-to-add-over-3000-employees-in-india/article29213780.ece | title=OYO to add over 3,000 employees in India |  work=[[Business Line]] | date=21 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://kr-asia.com/oyo-plans-mass-recruitment-in-india-to-boast-of-12k-staff-by-year-end | title=OYO plans mass recruitment in India to boast of 12k staff by year-end |  work=KrASIA | date=22 August 2019}}</ref> of which approximately 8000 are in India and South Asia. OYO Hotels & Homes now identifies as a full-fledged [[hotel chain]] that leases and franchises assets. The company claims to invest in capex,<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.businesstoday.in/current/corporate/oyo-rooms-hospitality-startup-collection-o-hotels-india-south-asia-oyo-announces-rs-1400-crore-investments-launches-new-property-collection-o-targeting-millennials/story/326986.html | title=OYO announces Rs 1,400 crore investments, launches new property 'Collection O' targeting millennials |  work=[[Business Today (India)]] | date=26 June 2019}}</ref> GMs to oversee operations and customer experience as well as generating around a million job opportunities in India<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/startups/newsbuzz/have-created-over-1-lakh-direct-and-indirect-jobs-in-india-oyo/articleshow/68812105.cms | title=Have created over 1 lakh direct and indirect jobs in India: OYO |  work=[[The Economic Times]] | date=10 April 2019}}</ref> and South Asia alone. OYO has also set up 26 training institutes for hospitality enthusiasts across India.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/companies/OYO-opens-Gurgaon-campus-with-plans-to-launch-a-skill-training-centre/articleshow/54020092.cms | title=OYO opens Gurgaon campus, plans to launch a skill training center |  work=[[The Times of India]] | date=6 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Funding==\nThe company is currently valued at $10&nbsp;billion<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://techcrunch.com/2019/07/19/indias-oyo-valued-at-10b-after-founder-purchases-2b-in-shares/ | title=India's Oyo valued at $10B after founder purchases $2B in shares |  work=[[TechCrunch]] | date=19 July 2019}}</ref> as per the last round of funding.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://techcrunch.com/2018/09/25/oyo-raises-1-billion/ | title=India's budget hotel startup OYO raises $1B for international growth |  work=[[TechCrunch]] | date=25 September 2018}}</ref>\n\nSeptember 2018 \u2013 raised $1&nbsp;billion, of which the RoC filing for the amount of $100&nbsp;million raised from Star Virtue Investment Ltd. was made on 13 February 2019.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.moneycontrol.com/news/business/chinas-didi-chuxing-invests-100-million-in-oyo-3537511.html | title=China's Didi Chuxing invests $100&nbsp;million in Oyo |  work=[[Moneycontrol.com]] | date=14 February 2019 |accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOctober 2019 \u2013 Series F funding of $1.5&nbsp;billion led by SoftBank Group, Lightspeed Venture Partners and Sequoia India.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://social.techcrunch.com/2019/10/07/india-oyo-ritesh-agarwal-investment/|title=Ritesh Agarwal to invest $700M in Oyo's new $1.5B financing round|website=TechCrunch|language=en-US|access-date=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n \nFounder & CEO, Ritesh Agarwal, through RA Hospitality Holdings (Cayman)<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/articleshow/70253747.cms | title=Ritesh Agarwal's Cayman based firm to bring funds to Oyo | work=[[The Economic Times]] | date=17 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/ritesh-agarwal-sets-ra-hospitality-cayman-islands-drive-oyo-funding-801845 | title=Ritesh Agarwal sets up RA Hospitality in Cayman Islands to drive Oyo funding |  work=[[International Business Times]] | date=18 July 2019}}</ref> in 2019 signed a $2&nbsp;billion primary and secondary management investment round, supported by global institutional banks and his financial partners, subject to regulatory and shareholder approvals. Lightspeed Venture Partners, and Sequoia India, OYO's early supporters, are selling part of their holdings in order to help the founder increase his stake and thereby commitment while remaining invested significantly in the company's long-term mission.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/companies/ritesh-agarwal-to-deploy-2-billion-in-his-hotel-startup-oyo-to-boost-stake-119071901295_1.html | title=Ritesh Agarwal to deploy $2&nbsp;billion in his hotel startup OYO to boost stake|work=[[Business Standard]]|date=19 July 2019|accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Financial results==\nIn 2019, OYO registered a revenue of USD 951 million, a 4.5 times increase on a year on year basis, as compared to USD 211 million.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.financialexpress.com/industry/sme/oyo-has-seen-4-4-times-y-o-y-growth-in-revenue-in-june-2019-says-founder-and-group-ceo-ritesh-agarwal/1716555/ | title=OYO has seen 4.4 times y-o-y growth in revenue in June 2019, says founder and group CEO Ritesh Agarwal | work=[[The Financial Express (India)|The Financial Express]] | date=25 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n\n==Appointments==\n\n===Rohit Kapoor===\nIn December  2019, Rohit Kapoor was appointed as the CEO for India & South Asia OYO Hotels & Homes<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.hospitalitynet.org/appointment/79019633.html | title=Rohit Kapoor Named CEO India and South Asia\nAt OYO Hotels & Homes in Gurgaon , India |  work=Hospitality Net | date=3 December 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/startups/newsbuzz/oyo-elevates-its-india-and-south-asia-head-aditya-ghosh-to-its-board/articleshow/72329724.cms | title=OYO: Aditya Ghosh on Oyo Board, Rohit Kapoor named new CEO |  work=[[The Economic Times]] | date=3 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Aditya Ghosh===\nIn December 2019, Aditya Ghosh was elevated to the Board of Directors (Earlier CEO India & South Asia)<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.livemint.com/companies/start-ups/oyo-shifts-aditya-ghosh-from-ceo-to-board-member-11575306726675.html | title=Oyo shifts Aditya Ghosh from CEO to board member |  work=[[Mint (newspaper)|Mint]] | date=2 December 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=http://www.businessworld.in/article/OYO-Elevates-Aditya-Ghosh-To-The-Board/02-12-2019-179637/ | title=OYO Elevates Aditya Ghosh To The Board |  work=[[Businessworld]] | date=2 December 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/company/corporate-trends/a-pin-up-ceo-parachuted-to-the-board-aditya-ghosh-takes-a-back-seat-in-oyo/articleshow/73753515.cms | title=OYO: A pin up CEO parachuted to the board, Aditya Ghosh takes a back seat in Oyo |  work=[[The Economic Times]] | date=30 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Ankit Gupta===\nIn December, OYO Appointed Ankit Gupta as the Chief Operating Officer & SVP for it\u2019s Frontier Businesses, OYO India & South Asia.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.moneycontrol.com/news/business/oyo-appoints-ankit-gupta-as-coo-4750181.html | title=OYO appoints Ankit Gupta as COO |  work=[[Moneycontrol.com]] | date=20 December 2020}}</ref>\n\nFurther, the company elevated Abhinav Ankur to Head - Strategy for OYO India & South Asia, Sharad Saxena to Chief Supply Officer - Franchise business, South Asia and Asit Biswal to Chief Supply Officer - Frontier Businesses, South Asia, OYO Hotels & Homes.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.peoplemattersglobal.com/news/leadership/oyo-strengthens-its-leadership-table-for-india-sa-business-24256 | title=OYO strengthens its leadership table for India & SA business |  work=[[People Matters]] | date=7 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ani/oyo-strengthens-its-leadership-table-for-india-and-sa-business-120010701175_1.html | title=OYO strengthens leadership table for India, SA and UK-Europe businesses |  work=[[Business Standard]] | date=8 January 2020}}</ref>\n \n===Rishabh Gupta===\nIn January 2020, OYO appointed Rishabh Gupta as the Country Head, UK & Ireland, OYO Hotels & Homes. Rishabh had been earlier entrusted with introducing and launching OYO in Indonesia.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.thecaterer.com/news/rishabh-gupta-joins-oyo | title=Oyo appoints new UK boss |  work=[[The Caterer]] | date=13 December 2019}}</ref>\n \n===Raj Kamal===\nIn January 2020, OYO appointed Raj Kamal as Chief Operating Officer for OYO\u2019s Vacation Homes business in the UK and Europe.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.cnbctv18.com/startup/after-aditya-ghosh-ritesh-agarwals-oyo-appoints-raj-kamal-as-coo-from-payu-5025171.htm | title=OYO appoints Raj Kamal from PayU as COO for UK and Europe business |  work=[[CNBC TV18]] | date=9 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Management==\nIn 2018, the hospitality chain company announced the appointment of [[Aditya Ghosh]], the former [[President (corporate title)|president]] of India's largest airlines, [[IndiGo]], as the [[chief executive officer]] of its South Asia business. Ghosh would be in charge of India and Nepal.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.ndtv.com/business/oyo-hotels-ceo-appointment-former-indigo-president-aditya-ghosh-joins-oyo-hotels-1948049 | title=OYO Hotels Appoints Former IndiGo President Aditya Ghosh As CEO-South Asia\n | work=[[NDTV]] | date=15 November 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2018, OYO appointed [[Max Healthcare]] executive Director, and Rohit Kapoor as the CEO<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.businesstoday.in/top-story/oyo-appoints-max-healthcare-rohit-kapoor-as-ceo-of-new-real-estate-business/story/294998.html | title=OYO reports revenues of Rs 327 crore in FY18OYO appoints Max Healthcare's Rohit Kapoor as CEO of new real estate business |  work=[[Business Today (India)]] | date=27 November 2018}}</ref> of its new real estate businesses. In 2018, OYO hired Prasidha Menon as Global Head of Communications.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ani/oyo-appoints-prasidha-menon-as-head-of-communications-118082700448_1.html | title=OYO appoints Prasidha Menon as Head of Communications |  work=[[Business Today (India)]] | date=27 August 2018}}</ref>\n\n===CTO===\nIn 2016, OYO announced the hire of Amazon India's Anil Goel as Chief Technical and Product Officer.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ani/oyo-hires-anil-goel-as-chief-technical-officer-116110700591_1.html | title=OYO hires Anil Goel as Chief Technology Officer |  work=[[Business Standard]] | date=7 November 2016}}</ref>\n\n===COO OYO China===\nOYO hired former Pepsi China COO to head its China operations as chief operating officer.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://tech.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/startups/oyo-bulks-up-international-leadership-with-key-hires/67460833 | title=OYO bulks up international leadership with key hires |  work=[[The Economic Times]] | date=10 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n===OYO UK===\nIn September 2018, OYO hired Jeremy Sanders<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-britain-hotels-oyo/indias-largest-hotel-chain-oyo-to-expand-into-britain-idUKKCN1LZ1FX | title=India's largest hotel chain OYO to expand into Britain |  work=[[Reuters]] | date=19 September 2018}}</ref> who co-founded and sold Italian [[fast-food]] chain Coco di Mama as its country head.\n\nIn January 2020, OYO announced the appointment of Raj Kamal as COO of its Vacation Homes business in the UK and Europe.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.businessworld.in/article/OYO-Appoints-Raj-Kamal-As-Chief-Operating-Officer/09-01-2020-181783/|title=OYO Appoints Raj Kamal As Chief Operating Officer|last=|first=|date=9 January 2020|work=BW Business World|access-date=9 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===CEO OYO Technology and Hospitality Company, Japan===\nIn February 2019, OYO started its Japan operations in a Joint Venture with Yahoo! Japan<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://skift.com/2019/02/22/oyo-partners-with-yahoo-to-bring-its-new-home-rental-model-to-japan/ | title=Oyo Partners With Yahoo to Bring Its New Home Rental Model to Japan |  work=[[skift]] | date=22 February 2019}}</ref> and hired former Japan market leader for Handy and [[Booking.com]], as the CEO of OYO Technology & Hospitality Company. Yahoo! has since sold its interest back to OYO as of December 2019.\n\n===CEO Southeast Asia and Middle East===\nIn August 2019, OYO hired Dr Mandar Vaidya<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/pti-stories/oyo-appoints-mandar-vaidya-as-ceo-for-southeast-asia-middle-east-119080700794_1.html | title=Oyo Partners With Yahoo to Bring Its New Home Rental Model to JapanOYO appoints Mandar Vaidya as CEO for South East and West Asia |  work=[[Business Standard]] | date=7 August 2019}}</ref> \u2013 a [[medical doctor]] by education and former partner at [[McKinsey]] \u2013 to lead its operations in Southeast Asia and the Middle East.\n\n==Acquisitions and partnerships==\nIn March 2018, OYO acquired [[Chennai]]-based [[service apartment]] operator Novascotia Boutique Homes<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/services/hotels-/-restaurants/oyo-acquires-chennais-novascotia-boutique-homes/articleshow/63358150.cms | title=OYO acquires Chennai's Novascotia Boutique Homes | first=Biswarup | last=Gooptu | work=[[The Economic Times]] | date=18 March 2018|accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/oyo-acquires-chennai-based-novascotia-boutique-homes-expand-corporate-offering-78171 | title=Oyo acquires Chennai-based Novascotia Boutique Homes to expand corporate offering | work=[[The News Minute]] | date=19 March 2018 |accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref> marking its first major buyout as well as establishing its presence in the service apartment and corporate executive stay.\n\nIn 2018, the company acquired Weddingz.in, a Mumbai-based online marketplace for wedding venues and vendors marking its entry into the fragmented $40&nbsp;billion wedding industry.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/startups/newsbuzz/oyo-acquires-wedding-marketplace-weddingz/articleshow/65361237.cms | title=OYO acquires wedding marketplace Weddingz | work=[[The Economic Times]] | date=11 August 2018|accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2019, OYO announced a strategic global distribution partnership with bedbank Hotelbeds.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/startups/newsbuzz/hotelbeds-oyo-hotels-homes-announce-strategic-distribution-partnership/articleshow/68888428.cms | title=Hotelbeds & Oyo Hotels & Homes announce strategic distribution partnership | work=[[The Economic Times]] | date=15 April 2019|accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref> The company also announced two joint-venture with Softbank and Yahoo!Japan.\n\nIn 2019, OYO and Airbnb announced a strategic partnership with Airbnb investing in OYO and the company will list their properties on Airbnb platform.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://techcrunch.com/2019/04/01/airbnb-oyo-investment/ | title=Airbnb confirms stake in India's OYO, sources say it invested $150M-$200M | work=[[Techcrunch]] | date=1 April 2019 |accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref>\nOYO in March 2019, announced a 1400 cr investment in its India and South Asia businesses over 2019 as a part of its efforts to increase infrastructure, strengthen technology and internal capability.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.thehindu.com/business/oyo-plans-1400-cr-expansion/article26514953.ece | title=OYO plans \u20b91,400-cr. expansion | work=[[The Hindu]] |date=12 March 2019 |accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2019, OYO announced the acquisition of Amsterdam-based @Leisure Group, Europe's largest vacation rental company.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/startups/newsbuzz/oyo-to-acquire-amsterdam-based-vacation-rental-company-leisure-group/articleshow/69129470.cms | title=OYO plans \u20b91,400-cr. expansion | work=[[The Economic Times]] | date=2 May 2019 |accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2019, OYO announced the acquisition of Innov8.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://techcrunch.com/2019/07/16/oyo-workspaces-innov8/ | title=India's budget hotel startup Oyo enters co-working business with $30 million Innov8 acquisition |work=[[Tech Crunch]] |date=16 July 2019 |accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2019, Oyo made its first major investment in the United States by purchasing the [[Hooters Casino Hotel]], near the [[Las Vegas Strip]], in partnership with US-based real estate company Highgate, for $135&nbsp;million.<ref>{{Cite web| url=https://www.livemint.com/companies/news/softbank-backed-oyo-known-for-budget-stays-to-rebrand-hooters-hotel-in-vegas-1566561488306.html | title=Oyo buys Las Vegas Hooters Hotel in its first US purchase|date=23 August 2019 | access-date=29 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/indias-oyo-rolls-dice-with-purchase-of-las-vegas-hooters-hotel-11566552601|title=India's Oyo Rolls Dice With Purchase of Las Vegas Hooters Hotel|last=Morris|first=Keiko|website=WSJ|language=en-US|access-date=29 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Products and services==\nOYO Rooms, OYO Hotels & Homes has a multi-brand approach. These include:\n* '''OYO Townhouse'''<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/startups/oyo-launches-oyo-townhouse/articleshow/56756602.cms | title=Budget hotel chain OYO launches OYO Townhouse | work=[[The Economic Times]] | date=24 January 2017}}</ref> which is promoted as the neighbourhood hotel is in the midscale segment targeted at millennial traveller aspiring premium economy accommodations.\n* '''OYO Home''', which OYO claims is India's maiden Home Management System that offers private homes in different locations and are fully managed by OYO.<ref>{{Cite news| url=https://qz.com/1077354/oyo-rooms-wants-to-build-an-airbnb-for-india-that-does-more-than-what-airbnb-does/ | title=In trying to be the Indian Airbnb, OYO may be turning too cumbersome | last=Bhattacharya| first=Ananya |work=[[Quartz Media]] | date=21 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.oyorooms.com/officialoyoblog/2017/09/15/oyo-home-unlocking-and-managing-homes-to-create-high-quality-spaces-for-our-guests-2 | title=Unlocking Homes for Great Holiday Experiences | work=OYO Rooms | date=15 September 2017}}</ref>\n* '''OYO Vacation Homes''' which identifies itself as the world's 3rd largest vacation home brand with vacation rental management brands Belvilla,<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://techcrunch.com/2019/05/01/airbnb-backed-oyo-moves-into-europe-acquires-leisure-from-axel-springer-for-415m/ | title=Airbnb-backed OYO moves into Europe, buys Leisure Group from Axel Springer for $415M | work=[[TechCrunch]] | date=1 May 2019}}</ref> Danland,<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/startups/newsbuzz/oyo-to-acquire-amsterdam-based-vacation-rental-company-leisure-group/articleshow/69129470.cms | title=OYO to acquire Amsterdam based vacation rental company @Leisure Group | work=[[The Economic Times]] | date=2 May 2019}}</ref> and DanCenter<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://techcrunch.com/2019/08/14/oyo-vacation-rental-europe/ | title=Oyo to invest $335M in vacation rental business in Europe push | work=[[TechCrunch]] | date=14 August 2019}}</ref> along with Germany-based Traum-Ferienwohnungen.\n* '''SilverKey''' launched in April 2018, caters to the needs of the corporate travellers undertaking business trips for a short or long duration.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/startups/newsbuzz/oyo-to-scale-up-its-silverkey-hotels-portfolio-to-19-cities-across-india/articleshow/68698845.cms | title=OYO to scale up its SilverKey hotels portfolio to 19 cities across India | work=[[The Economic Times]] | date=3 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/companies/oyo-plans-big-focus-on-serviced-apartments-for-corporate-clients-118041800353_1.html | title=OYO plans big focus on serviced apartments for corporate clients | work=[[Business Standard]] | date=18 April 2018}}</ref>\n* '''Capital O''' are premium hotels located in prime locations and especially curated to deliver OYO's quality-assured experience at an affordable price.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.arabianbusiness.com/travel-hospitality/423960-indias-oyo-launches-capital-o-hotels-in-the-uae | title=India's Oyo launches Capital O hotels in the UAE | work=[[Arabian Business]] | date=16 July 2019}}</ref>\n* '''Palette''' offers the perfectly curated staycation for those in search of an intuitive experience at competitive prices, an upper-end leisure resorts category.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/business/india-business/oyo-forays-into-leisure-segment-with-palette-resorts/articleshow/65607782.cms | title=Oyo forays into leisure segment with Palette Resorts | work=[[The Times of India]] | date=30 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/startups/newsbuzz/oyo-forays-into-upper-end-leisure-resorts-category-launches-palette-resorts/articleshow/65607265.cms | title=OYO forays into upper-end leisure resorts category; launches Palette Resorts | work=[[The Economic Times]] | date=30 August 2018}}</ref>\n* '''Collection O''' is the newest category under OYO's hotel portfolio that caters to the requirements of discerning business travellers.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/nation/current-affairs/130319/oyo-woos-biz-travellers-with-collection-o-ups-investment.html | title=OYO woos biz travellers with Collection O; ups investment | work=[[Deccan Chronicle]] | date=13 March 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.aninews.in/news/business/oyos-collection-o-hotels-reaches-milestone-175-buildings-in-3-months20190713124833/ | title=OYO's Collection O Hotels reaches milestone 175 buildings in 3 months | work=[[Asian News International]] | date=13 July 2019}}</ref>\n* '''OYO LIFE''', targeted at millennials and young professionals in search of fully managed homes on long-term rentals, at affordable prices. This is a PG based model where you can take a room or share it with a friend without any restrictions<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/why-oyo-life-betting-big-co-living-market-india-101514 | title=Why OYO Life is betting big on the co-living market in India | work=[[The News Minute]] | date=9 May 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/startups/newsbuzz/oyo-looks-to-enter-student-housing-and-co-working-to-expand-co-living-segments/articleshow/69172676.cms | title=Oyo looks to enter student housing and co-working, to expand co-living segments | work=[[The Economic Times]] | date=6 May 2019}}</ref>\n*OYO has grouped all its products into a single category, that is OYO Rooms and homes.{{cn|date=March 2020}}\n\n==OYO Partner Engagement==\nIn April 2019, the company announced the launch of OPEN programme, an initiative for its partner hotels to help them reach their business goals. It further Introduced upgraded Co-OYO app for hotel partners to provide complete visibility on all business & customer metrics. <ref>{{Cite news | url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/startups/newsbuzz/oyo-launches-open-programme-for-asset-owners/articleshow/68937688.cms | title=OYO launches OPEN programme for asset owners |  work=[[The Economic Times]] | date=18 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Awards and honours==\n* In 2019 Agarwal was featured in the Bloomberg 50 list as \u2018The Amazingly Ambitious Hotelier\u2019,<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.bloombergquint.com/businessweek/ritesh-agarwal-s-oyo-rooms-is-poised-to-overtake-marriott | title=Ritesh Agarwal, the Amazingly Ambitious Hotelier | work=BloombergQuint | date=4 December 2019}}</ref> the 50 most powerful people in India by India Today and the Tycoons of Tomorrow\u2019 by Forbes India.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.forbesindia.com/lists/tycoons-of-tomorrow/1729/1|title=Tycoons of Tomorrow|website=Forbes India|language=en-US|access-date=10 December 2019}}</ref>\n* His net worth in 2019 was estimated to be approximately $1&nbsp;billion (7000 crore INR) according to IIFL Wealth Hurun India Rich List.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.outlookindia.com/outlookmoney/talking-money/iifl-wealth-hurun-india-rich-list-2019-all-you-need-to-know-3619 | title=IIFL Wealth Hurun India Rich List 2019: All You Need To Know | work=Outlook (Indian magazine) | date=26 September 2019}}</ref>\n* Market Entrant of the Year 2019 (UK-India Awards)<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.hotelowner.co.uk/22072-oyo-hotels-wins-market-entrant-of-the-year-at-uk-india-awards/ | title=OYO Hotels wins 'Market Entrant of the Year' at UK-India Awards | work=Hotel Owner | date=2 July 2019}}</ref>\n* Fast Company's World's Most Innovative Companies for 2019 \u2013 India edition<ref>{{Cite web| url=https://www.fastcompany.com/most-innovative-companies/2019/sectors/india | title=The World's Most Innovative Companies 2019: India Honorees|date=20 September 2019 | access-date=20 September 2019}}</ref>\n* Best Startup \u2013 SATTE Awards 2019<ref>{{Cite news | url=http://www.satteawards.com/winners-2019.html | title=Best Startup \u2013 SATTE Awards 2019 | date=16 January 2019}}</ref>\n* OYO topped the maiden list of LinkedIn's Top Startups in India (2018)<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.moneycontrol.com/news/business/linkedin-says-these-are-the-25-most-attractive-startups-to-work-for-in-india-2961531.html | title=LinkedIn says these are the 25 most attractive startups to work for in India | date=18 September 2018}}</ref>\n* LinkedIn has recognized OYO as one of the top employee attractors in India four years in a row (2016, 2017, 2018, 2019)<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://lists.linkedin.com/2016/top-attractors/en/india/oyorooms | title=Top Attractors Where India Wants to Work Now | work=[[LinkedIn]] | date=3 April 2019}}</ref>\n* Fast Company: OYO among Top 10 Most Innovative Companies in India (2018)<ref>{{Cite web| url=https://www.fastcompany.com/most-innovative-companies/2018/sectors/india | title=THE WORLD'S MOST INNOVATIVE COMPANIES 2018 |date=20 September 2019 | access-date=20 September 2019}}</ref>\n* Startup of the Year at The Economic Times Startup Awards (2018)<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/startups/newsbuzz/oyo-books-top-spot-at-et-startup-awards/articleshow/65127601.cms | title=OYO books top spot at ET Startup Awards 2018 | work=[[The Economic Times]] | date=25 July 2019}}</ref>\n* TiE's QGlue Design-led Entrepreneurship Awards (2018)<ref>{{Cite web| url=http://excellenceawards.tiecon-delhi.org/design/ | title=TiE Global Summit 3 2018 |date=20 September 2019 | access-date=20 September 2019}}</ref>\n* Best Travel Startup \u2013 Jury at Zee Business Travel Awards (2018)<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://zeenews.india.com/travel/zee-business-travel-awards-heres-the-complete-list-of-winners-2142817.htm | title=Zee Business Travel Awards: Here's the complete list of winners | work=[[Zee News]] | date=22 September 2018}}</ref>\n* India's Most Promising Hotel Network, HolidayIQ Better Holiday Awards 2017<ref>{{Cite web| url=https://www.oyorooms.com/officialoyoblog/2017/05/16/oyo-named-the-most-promising-hotel-network | title=OYO VOTED THE MOST PROMISING HOTEL NETWORK |date=16 May 2017 | access-date=20 September 2019}}</ref>\n* New Age Entrepreneur Award by Asian Centre for Corporate Governance & Sustainability (2016)<ref>{{Cite web| url=http://www.asiancentre.org/asiasummit/ | title=Asian Centre for Corporate Governance &#038; Sustainability: 4th Asia Business Responsibility Summit |date=20 September 2019 | access-date=20 September 2019}}</ref>\n* OneDirect Quest CX Award for Best Use of Social Media (2016)<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://inc42.com/buzz/onedirect-quest/ | title=OneDirect organised the Second Edition of Quest \u2013 India's largest Customer Experience Management Summit | work=Inc42 | date=27 April 2016}}</ref>\n* No. 2 in BT Coolest Start-ups Survey 2016<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.businesstoday.in/photos/coolest-start-ups/coolest-start-ups-of-india-2016/1075.html#photo2 | title=Coolest Start-Ups of India 2016 | work=[[Business Today (India)]] | date=27 April 2016}}</ref>\n* Startup of the Year- Express IT Award (2015)<ref>{{Cite web| url=http://expressitawards.financialexpress.com/winner2015/ | title=Winners 2015 \u2013 Express I.T Awards  |date=20 September 2017 | access-date=20 September 2019}}</ref>\n* In March 2020, [[Ivanka Trump]], the senior advisor to President [[Donald Trump]], had lauded an initiative by OYO Hotels to offer free stays to doctors, nurses in the US helping in the fight against the novel coronavirus, describing the gesture as \u201cimpactful acts of benevolence\u201d.<ref>{{cite news |title=Ivanka Trump lauds Indian hotel chain OYO for offering free stays to doctors in US amid COVID19 crisis |url=https://www.moneycontrol.com/news/business/ivanka-trump-lauds-indian-hotel-chain-oyo-for-offering-free-stays-to-doctors-in-us-amid-covid19-crisis-5070191.html |accessdate=26 March 2020 |work=Moneycontrol |date=25 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Controversies==\n===Sharing of customer data with the government===\nIn 2019, OYO rooms plans to implement a digital register mechanism which will allow it to share customer data in real time with the government. This has been described as a threat to privacy.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.indiatoday.in/technology/news/story/oyo-rooms-wants-to-share-digital-record-of-your-check-ins-with-government-1431439-2019-01-15 | title=Oyo Rooms wants to share digital record of your check-ins with government | work=[[India Today]] | date=15 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.indianpeopletimes.com/digital-world/oyorooms-with-new-concept-of-digital-data-sharing-with-government/ | title=Oyorooms with new concept of data sharing with government authorities | work=Indian people times | date=16 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Use of predatory pricing===\nOYO has been accused of using [[predatory pricing]] and not following its own agreements including threatening hotels to unilaterally change some of the clauses or not be paid.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/services/hotels-/-restaurants/budget-hotels-teaming-up-to-take-legal-route-against-oyo/articleshow/66890345.cms | title=Budget hotels teaming up to take legal route against Oyo | first=Anumeha | last=Chaturvedi | work=[[The Economic Times]] | date=1 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Sending of unsolicited emails===\nIn 2018, the company sent mass unsolicited job offer emails targeting senior- and mid-level employees of competitors.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.livemint.com/Industry/ML1hLZR50QT08vsDMPfSzK/Alls-fair-in-talent-war-Oyo-targets-staff-at-rivals.html | title=All's fair in talent war: Oyo targets staff at rivals | last=S.H. | first=Salman | work=[[Mint (newspaper)|Mint]] | date=27 April 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== Downsizing of OYO China ===\nIn March 2020, it was reported that OYO China will downsize and lay off up to 72% of its staff. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mingtiandi.com/real-estate/finance-real-estate/oyo-hotels-said-to-cut-over-72-of-china-staff/|title=Oyo Hotels Said to Cut Over 72% of China Staff|date=14 March 2020|website=Mingtiandi|language=en-US|access-date=19 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== ''Conservancy on Oyo Rooms privacy policy'' ==\nMany Customers claim that their private videos and images are leaked during they use Oyo Rooms Services. However, no concrete evidence has been found about these things and no action has been taken on them. But this thing cannot be ignored because many people have faced the problem this evening.\n<br />\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Official website}}\n\n{{SoftBank}}\n{{Hospitality_service}}\n\n[[Category:Hotel affiliation groups]]\n[[Category:Hotel chains in India]]\n[[Category:Indian companies established in 2013]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Gurgaon]]\n[[Category:Softbank portfolio companies]]\n[[Category:Indian brands]]\n[[Category:Hotels in India]]\n[[Category:Hospitality companies of India]]\n[[Category:Hospitality companies of Asia]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Indian hospitality company}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name        = Oyo Rooms\n| logo        = OYO Rooms (logo).png\n| logo_size   = \n| type        = [[Privately held company]]\n| trade_name  = OYO Rooms<br>OYO Hotels and Homes\n| industry    = [[Hospitality industry|Hospitality]]\n| founded     = {{start date and age|df=yes|2013}}\n| location    = [[Gurgaon, Haryana]], India\n| founder     = [[Ritesh Agarwal]]\n| key_people  = Ritesh Agarwal (CEO)\n| area_served = [[Asia]], [[Europe]] and [[America]]s\n| website     = {{url|www.oyorooms.com}}\n}}\n[[File:OYO Fenglin Hotel in Changshu.jpg|thumb|OYO in [[Changshu]], [[Jiangsu]], [[China]]]]\n'''Oyo Rooms''' (stylised as '''OYO'''), also known as '''Oyo Homes & Hotels''', is an Indian hotel chain. It is one of the largest and fastest-growing hospitality chain of leased and franchised hotels, homes and living spaces.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ft.com/content/e515c058-5e24-11ea-b0ab-339c2307bcd4|title=Subscribe to read {{!}} Financial Times|website=www.ft.com|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.moneycontrol.com/news/business/oyo-says-it-is-worlds-3rd-largest-hotel-chain-by-room-count-4191531.html|title=With 8.5 lakh rooms, Oyo claims third spot globally|date=10 July 2019|work=[[Moneycontrol.com]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.financialexpress.com/industry/sme/how-oyo-became-indias-3rd-best-company-to-work-for-in-just-6-years/1540659/|title=How OYO became India's 3rd best company to work for in just 6 years|date=7 April 2019|work=[[The Financial Express (India)]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last1=Gooptu|first1=Biswarup|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/startups/newsbuzz/have-become-the-second-largest-hotel-group-in-china-oyo/articleshow/69445392.cms|title=OYO claims to be second-largest hotel group in China|date=22 May 2019|newspaper=[[The Economic Times]]}}</ref> Founded in 2013 by [[Ritesh Agarwal]], OYO initially consisted mainly of budget hotels. The startup expanded globally with thousands of [[hotels]], [[vacation homes]] and millions of rooms in hundreds of cities in India, Malaysia,<ref>{{Cite web | title=OYO Rooms Goes International; Launches in Malaysia | url=https://inc42.com/flash-feed/oyo-rooms-launches-operations-in-malaysia/ | first=Aparna | last=Mishra | work=Inc42 | date=12 January 2016}}</ref> UAE, Nepal,<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/companies/oyo-expands-international-presence-with-hotel-launch-in-nepal-117042700475_1.html | title=OYO expands international presence with hotel launch in Nepal | work=[[Business Standard]] | date=27 April 2017}}</ref> China, Brazil, Mexico, UK, Philippines, Japan,<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/startups/newsbuzz/oyo-commences-hotel-operations-in-japan/articleshow/68716847.cms | title=OYO and SoftBank form JV to launch hotels business in Japan |  work=[[The Economic Times]] | date=4 April 2019}}</ref> Saudi Arabia, Sri Lanka,<ref>{{Cite news | url=http://www.dailymirror.lk/article/OYO-expands-international-presence-entering-Sri-Lanka-159788.html | title=OYO expands international presence entering Sri Lanka |  work=[[Daily Mirror]] | date=14 December 2018}}</ref> Indonesia, Vietnam, the United States<ref>{{Cite web | title=Hotel Unicorn Oyo Plots $300 Million Push into the U.S. Market | url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2019-06-19/hotel-unicorn-oyo-plots-300-million-push-into-the-u-s-market | work=[[Bloomberg L.P]] | date=19 June 2019}}</ref> and more.<ref>{{Cite web | title=More room at the top | url=https://www.fortuneindia.com/venture/more-room-at-the-top/101637 | first=DEEPTI | last=CHAUDHARY | work=[[Fortune (magazine)|Fortune]] | date=2 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.ndtv.com/people/at-21-hes-the-mind-behind-multi-million-dollar-start-up-oyo-1204353 | title=At 21, He's the Mind Behind Multi-Million Dollar Start-Up OYO | first=Natasha | last=Jog | work=[[NDTV]] | date=6 August 2015}}</ref> \n\nThe company's investors include [[SoftBank Group]], Greenoaks Capital, Sequoia India, Lightspeed India, Hero Enterprise, [[Airbnb]] and [[China Lodging Group]].\n\n==History==\nIn 2012, Ritesh Agarwal launched Oravel Stays to enable listing and booking of budget accommodations. After undertaking months of research and staying in various [[bed and breakfast]] homes, [[guest house]]s, and small hotels across India, he pivoted Oravel to OYO in 2013.<ref>{{Cite news | url=http://www.forbesindia.com/article/8th-anniversary-special/how-oyos-ritesh-agarwal-transformed-the-business-of-budget-accommodation/46971/1 | title=How OYO's Ritesh Agarwal transformed the business of budget accommodation | first=PARAMITA | last=CHATTERJEE | work=[[Forbes]] | date=16 May 2017}}</ref>\n\nOYO partners with hotels to give similar guest experience across cities. Shortly after launching Oravel Stays, Ritesh Agarwal received a grant of [[United States dollar|$]]100,000 as part of the [[Thiel Fellowship]] from [[Peter Thiel]].<ref>{{Cite news | title=Oravel founder Ritesh Agarwal wins Thiel Fellowship | url=https://www.livemint.com/Companies/ZbqDGYUN0yfhtB2syOIDVP/Oravel-founder-Ritesh-Agarwal-wins-Thiel-Fellowship.html | work=[[Mint (newspaper)|Mint]] | date=10 May 2013}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.businessinsider.com/ritesh-agarwal-interview-with-founder-of-peter-thiel-backed-oyo-2018-9 | title=Ritesh Agarwal: Interview with founder of Peter Thiel-backed Oyo | first=Shona | last=Ghosh | work=[[Business Insider]] | date=22 September 2018 | url-access=subscription}}</ref> OYO currently has over 17,000 employees globally,<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/companies/oyo-to-add-over-3000-employees-in-india/article29213780.ece | title=OYO to add over 3,000 employees in India |  work=[[Business Line]] | date=21 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://kr-asia.com/oyo-plans-mass-recruitment-in-india-to-boast-of-12k-staff-by-year-end | title=OYO plans mass recruitment in India to boast of 12k staff by year-end |  work=KrASIA | date=22 August 2019}}</ref> of which approximately 8000 are in India and South Asia. OYO Hotels & Homes now identifies as a full-fledged [[hotel chain]] that leases and franchises assets. The company claims to invest in capex,<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.businesstoday.in/current/corporate/oyo-rooms-hospitality-startup-collection-o-hotels-india-south-asia-oyo-announces-rs-1400-crore-investments-launches-new-property-collection-o-targeting-millennials/story/326986.html | title=OYO announces Rs 1,400 crore investments, launches new property 'Collection O' targeting millennials |  work=[[Business Today (India)]] | date=26 June 2019}}</ref> GMs to oversee operations and customer experience as well as generating around a million job opportunities in India<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/startups/newsbuzz/have-created-over-1-lakh-direct-and-indirect-jobs-in-india-oyo/articleshow/68812105.cms | title=Have created over 1 lakh direct and indirect jobs in India: OYO |  work=[[The Economic Times]] | date=10 April 2019}}</ref> and South Asia alone. OYO has also set up 26 training institutes for hospitality enthusiasts across India.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/companies/OYO-opens-Gurgaon-campus-with-plans-to-launch-a-skill-training-centre/articleshow/54020092.cms | title=OYO opens Gurgaon campus, plans to launch a skill training center |  work=[[The Times of India]] | date=6 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Funding==\nThe company is currently valued at $10&nbsp;billion<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://techcrunch.com/2019/07/19/indias-oyo-valued-at-10b-after-founder-purchases-2b-in-shares/ | title=India's Oyo valued at $10B after founder purchases $2B in shares |  work=[[TechCrunch]] | date=19 July 2019}}</ref> as per the last round of funding.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://techcrunch.com/2018/09/25/oyo-raises-1-billion/ | title=India's budget hotel startup OYO raises $1B for international growth |  work=[[TechCrunch]] | date=25 September 2018}}</ref>\n\nSeptember 2018 \u2013 raised $1&nbsp;billion, of which the RoC filing for the amount of $100&nbsp;million raised from Star Virtue Investment Ltd. was made on 13 February 2019.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.moneycontrol.com/news/business/chinas-didi-chuxing-invests-100-million-in-oyo-3537511.html | title=China's Didi Chuxing invests $100&nbsp;million in Oyo |  work=[[Moneycontrol.com]] | date=14 February 2019 |accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOctober 2019 \u2013 Series F funding of $1.5&nbsp;billion led by SoftBank Group, Lightspeed Venture Partners and Sequoia India.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://social.techcrunch.com/2019/10/07/india-oyo-ritesh-agarwal-investment/|title=Ritesh Agarwal to invest $700M in Oyo's new $1.5B financing round|website=TechCrunch|language=en-US|access-date=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n \nFounder & CEO, Ritesh Agarwal, through RA Hospitality Holdings (Cayman)<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/articleshow/70253747.cms | title=Ritesh Agarwal's Cayman based firm to bring funds to Oyo | work=[[The Economic Times]] | date=17 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/ritesh-agarwal-sets-ra-hospitality-cayman-islands-drive-oyo-funding-801845 | title=Ritesh Agarwal sets up RA Hospitality in Cayman Islands to drive Oyo funding |  work=[[International Business Times]] | date=18 July 2019}}</ref> in 2019 signed a $2&nbsp;billion primary and secondary management investment round, supported by global institutional banks and his financial partners, subject to regulatory and shareholder approvals. Lightspeed Venture Partners, and Sequoia India, OYO's early supporters, are selling part of their holdings in order to help the founder increase his stake and thereby commitment while remaining invested significantly in the company's long-term mission.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/companies/ritesh-agarwal-to-deploy-2-billion-in-his-hotel-startup-oyo-to-boost-stake-119071901295_1.html | title=Ritesh Agarwal to deploy $2&nbsp;billion in his hotel startup OYO to boost stake|work=[[Business Standard]]|date=19 July 2019|accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Financial results==\nIn 2019, OYO registered a revenue of USD 951 million, a 4.5 times increase on a year on year basis, as compared to USD 211 million.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.financialexpress.com/industry/sme/oyo-has-seen-4-4-times-y-o-y-growth-in-revenue-in-june-2019-says-founder-and-group-ceo-ritesh-agarwal/1716555/ | title=OYO has seen 4.4 times y-o-y growth in revenue in June 2019, says founder and group CEO Ritesh Agarwal | work=[[The Financial Express (India)|The Financial Express]] | date=25 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n\n==Appointments==\n\n===Rohit Kapoor===\nIn December  2019, Rohit Kapoor was appointed as the CEO for India & South Asia OYO Hotels & Homes<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.hospitalitynet.org/appointment/79019633.html | title=Rohit Kapoor Named CEO India and South Asia\nAt OYO Hotels & Homes in Gurgaon , India |  work=Hospitality Net | date=3 December 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/startups/newsbuzz/oyo-elevates-its-india-and-south-asia-head-aditya-ghosh-to-its-board/articleshow/72329724.cms | title=OYO: Aditya Ghosh on Oyo Board, Rohit Kapoor named new CEO |  work=[[The Economic Times]] | date=3 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Aditya Ghosh===\nIn December 2019, Aditya Ghosh was elevated to the Board of Directors (Earlier CEO India & South Asia)<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.livemint.com/companies/start-ups/oyo-shifts-aditya-ghosh-from-ceo-to-board-member-11575306726675.html | title=Oyo shifts Aditya Ghosh from CEO to board member |  work=[[Mint (newspaper)|Mint]] | date=2 December 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=http://www.businessworld.in/article/OYO-Elevates-Aditya-Ghosh-To-The-Board/02-12-2019-179637/ | title=OYO Elevates Aditya Ghosh To The Board |  work=[[Businessworld]] | date=2 December 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/company/corporate-trends/a-pin-up-ceo-parachuted-to-the-board-aditya-ghosh-takes-a-back-seat-in-oyo/articleshow/73753515.cms | title=OYO: A pin up CEO parachuted to the board, Aditya Ghosh takes a back seat in Oyo |  work=[[The Economic Times]] | date=30 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Ankit Gupta===\nIn December, OYO Appointed Ankit Gupta as the Chief Operating Officer & SVP for it\u2019s Frontier Businesses, OYO India & South Asia.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.moneycontrol.com/news/business/oyo-appoints-ankit-gupta-as-coo-4750181.html | title=OYO appoints Ankit Gupta as COO |  work=[[Moneycontrol.com]] | date=20 December 2020}}</ref>\n\nFurther, the company elevated Abhinav Ankur to Head - Strategy for OYO India & South Asia, Sharad Saxena to Chief Supply Officer - Franchise business, South Asia and Asit Biswal to Chief Supply Officer - Frontier Businesses, South Asia, OYO Hotels & Homes.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.peoplemattersglobal.com/news/leadership/oyo-strengthens-its-leadership-table-for-india-sa-business-24256 | title=OYO strengthens its leadership table for India & SA business |  work=[[People Matters]] | date=7 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ani/oyo-strengthens-its-leadership-table-for-india-and-sa-business-120010701175_1.html | title=OYO strengthens leadership table for India, SA and UK-Europe businesses |  work=[[Business Standard]] | date=8 January 2020}}</ref>\n \n===Rishabh Gupta===\nIn January 2020, OYO appointed Rishabh Gupta as the Country Head, UK & Ireland, OYO Hotels & Homes. Rishabh had been earlier entrusted with introducing and launching OYO in Indonesia.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.thecaterer.com/news/rishabh-gupta-joins-oyo | title=Oyo appoints new UK boss |  work=[[The Caterer]] | date=13 December 2019}}</ref>\n \n===Raj Kamal===\nIn January 2020, OYO appointed Raj Kamal as Chief Operating Officer for OYO\u2019s Vacation Homes business in the UK and Europe.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.cnbctv18.com/startup/after-aditya-ghosh-ritesh-agarwals-oyo-appoints-raj-kamal-as-coo-from-payu-5025171.htm | title=OYO appoints Raj Kamal from PayU as COO for UK and Europe business |  work=[[CNBC TV18]] | date=9 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Management==\nIn 2018, the hospitality chain company announced the appointment of [[Aditya Ghosh]], the former [[President (corporate title)|president]] of India's largest airlines, [[IndiGo]], as the [[chief executive officer]] of its South Asia business. Ghosh would be in charge of India and Nepal.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.ndtv.com/business/oyo-hotels-ceo-appointment-former-indigo-president-aditya-ghosh-joins-oyo-hotels-1948049 | title=OYO Hotels Appoints Former IndiGo President Aditya Ghosh As CEO-South Asia\n | work=[[NDTV]] | date=15 November 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2018, OYO appointed [[Max Healthcare]] executive Director, and Rohit Kapoor as the CEO<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.businesstoday.in/top-story/oyo-appoints-max-healthcare-rohit-kapoor-as-ceo-of-new-real-estate-business/story/294998.html | title=OYO reports revenues of Rs 327 crore in FY18OYO appoints Max Healthcare's Rohit Kapoor as CEO of new real estate business |  work=[[Business Today (India)]] | date=27 November 2018}}</ref> of its new real estate businesses. In 2018, OYO hired Prasidha Menon as Global Head of Communications.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ani/oyo-appoints-prasidha-menon-as-head-of-communications-118082700448_1.html | title=OYO appoints Prasidha Menon as Head of Communications |  work=[[Business Today (India)]] | date=27 August 2018}}</ref>\n\n===CTO===\nIn 2016, OYO announced the hire of Amazon India's Anil Goel as Chief Technical and Product Officer.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ani/oyo-hires-anil-goel-as-chief-technical-officer-116110700591_1.html | title=OYO hires Anil Goel as Chief Technology Officer |  work=[[Business Standard]] | date=7 November 2016}}</ref>\n\n===COO OYO China===\nOYO hired former Pepsi China COO to head its China operations as chief operating officer.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://tech.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/startups/oyo-bulks-up-international-leadership-with-key-hires/67460833 | title=OYO bulks up international leadership with key hires |  work=[[The Economic Times]] | date=10 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n===OYO UK===\nIn September 2018, OYO hired Jeremy Sanders<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-britain-hotels-oyo/indias-largest-hotel-chain-oyo-to-expand-into-britain-idUKKCN1LZ1FX | title=India's largest hotel chain OYO to expand into Britain |  work=[[Reuters]] | date=19 September 2018}}</ref> who co-founded and sold Italian [[fast-food]] chain Coco di Mama as its country head.\n\nIn January 2020, OYO announced the appointment of Raj Kamal as COO of its Vacation Homes business in the UK and Europe.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.businessworld.in/article/OYO-Appoints-Raj-Kamal-As-Chief-Operating-Officer/09-01-2020-181783/|title=OYO Appoints Raj Kamal As Chief Operating Officer|last=|first=|date=9 January 2020|work=BW Business World|access-date=9 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===CEO OYO Technology and Hospitality Company, Japan===\nIn February 2019, OYO started its Japan operations in a Joint Venture with Yahoo! Japan<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://skift.com/2019/02/22/oyo-partners-with-yahoo-to-bring-its-new-home-rental-model-to-japan/ | title=Oyo Partners With Yahoo to Bring Its New Home Rental Model to Japan |  work=[[skift]] | date=22 February 2019}}</ref> and hired former Japan market leader for Handy and [[Booking.com]], as the CEO of OYO Technology & Hospitality Company. Yahoo! has since sold its interest back to OYO as of December 2019.\n\n===CEO Southeast Asia and Middle East===\nIn August 2019, OYO hired Dr Mandar Vaidya<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/pti-stories/oyo-appoints-mandar-vaidya-as-ceo-for-southeast-asia-middle-east-119080700794_1.html | title=Oyo Partners With Yahoo to Bring Its New Home Rental Model to JapanOYO appoints Mandar Vaidya as CEO for South East and West Asia |  work=[[Business Standard]] | date=7 August 2019}}</ref> \u2013 a [[medical doctor]] by education and former partner at [[McKinsey]] \u2013 to lead its operations in Southeast Asia and the Middle East.\n\n==Acquisitions and partnerships==\nIn March 2018, OYO acquired [[Chennai]]-based [[service apartment]] operator Novascotia Boutique Homes<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/services/hotels-/-restaurants/oyo-acquires-chennais-novascotia-boutique-homes/articleshow/63358150.cms | title=OYO acquires Chennai's Novascotia Boutique Homes | first=Biswarup | last=Gooptu | work=[[The Economic Times]] | date=18 March 2018|accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/oyo-acquires-chennai-based-novascotia-boutique-homes-expand-corporate-offering-78171 | title=Oyo acquires Chennai-based Novascotia Boutique Homes to expand corporate offering | work=[[The News Minute]] | date=19 March 2018 |accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref> marking its first major buyout as well as establishing its presence in the service apartment and corporate executive stay.\n\nIn 2018, the company acquired Weddingz.in, a Mumbai-based online marketplace for wedding venues and vendors marking its entry into the fragmented $40&nbsp;billion wedding industry.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/startups/newsbuzz/oyo-acquires-wedding-marketplace-weddingz/articleshow/65361237.cms | title=OYO acquires wedding marketplace Weddingz | work=[[The Economic Times]] | date=11 August 2018|accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2019, OYO announced a strategic global distribution partnership with bedbank Hotelbeds.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/startups/newsbuzz/hotelbeds-oyo-hotels-homes-announce-strategic-distribution-partnership/articleshow/68888428.cms | title=Hotelbeds & Oyo Hotels & Homes announce strategic distribution partnership | work=[[The Economic Times]] | date=15 April 2019|accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref> The company also announced two joint-venture with Softbank and Yahoo!Japan.\n\nIn 2019, OYO and Airbnb announced a strategic partnership with Airbnb investing in OYO and the company will list their properties on Airbnb platform.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://techcrunch.com/2019/04/01/airbnb-oyo-investment/ | title=Airbnb confirms stake in India's OYO, sources say it invested $150M-$200M | work=[[Techcrunch]] | date=1 April 2019 |accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref>\nOYO in March 2019, announced a 1400 cr investment in its India and South Asia businesses over 2019 as a part of its efforts to increase infrastructure, strengthen technology and internal capability.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.thehindu.com/business/oyo-plans-1400-cr-expansion/article26514953.ece | title=OYO plans \u20b91,400-cr. expansion | work=[[The Hindu]] |date=12 March 2019 |accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2019, OYO announced the acquisition of Amsterdam-based @Leisure Group, Europe's largest vacation rental company.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/startups/newsbuzz/oyo-to-acquire-amsterdam-based-vacation-rental-company-leisure-group/articleshow/69129470.cms | title=OYO plans \u20b91,400-cr. expansion | work=[[The Economic Times]] | date=2 May 2019 |accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2019, OYO announced the acquisition of Innov8.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://techcrunch.com/2019/07/16/oyo-workspaces-innov8/ | title=India's budget hotel startup Oyo enters co-working business with $30 million Innov8 acquisition |work=[[Tech Crunch]] |date=16 July 2019 |accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2019, Oyo made its first major investment in the United States by purchasing the [[Hooters Casino Hotel]], near the [[Las Vegas Strip]], in partnership with US-based real estate company Highgate, for $135&nbsp;million.<ref>{{Cite web| url=https://www.livemint.com/companies/news/softbank-backed-oyo-known-for-budget-stays-to-rebrand-hooters-hotel-in-vegas-1566561488306.html | title=Oyo buys Las Vegas Hooters Hotel in its first US purchase|date=23 August 2019 | access-date=29 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/indias-oyo-rolls-dice-with-purchase-of-las-vegas-hooters-hotel-11566552601|title=India's Oyo Rolls Dice With Purchase of Las Vegas Hooters Hotel|last=Morris|first=Keiko|website=WSJ|language=en-US|access-date=29 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Products and services==\nOYO Rooms, OYO Hotels & Homes has a multi-brand approach. These include:\n* '''OYO Townhouse'''<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/startups/oyo-launches-oyo-townhouse/articleshow/56756602.cms | title=Budget hotel chain OYO launches OYO Townhouse | work=[[The Economic Times]] | date=24 January 2017}}</ref> which is promoted as the neighbourhood hotel is in the midscale segment targeted at millennial traveller aspiring premium economy accommodations.\n* '''OYO Home''', which OYO claims is India's maiden Home Management System that offers private homes in different locations and are fully managed by OYO.<ref>{{Cite news| url=https://qz.com/1077354/oyo-rooms-wants-to-build-an-airbnb-for-india-that-does-more-than-what-airbnb-does/ | title=In trying to be the Indian Airbnb, OYO may be turning too cumbersome | last=Bhattacharya| first=Ananya |work=[[Quartz Media]] | date=21 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.oyorooms.com/officialoyoblog/2017/09/15/oyo-home-unlocking-and-managing-homes-to-create-high-quality-spaces-for-our-guests-2 | title=Unlocking Homes for Great Holiday Experiences | work=OYO Rooms | date=15 September 2017}}</ref>\n* '''OYO Vacation Homes''' which identifies itself as the world's 3rd largest vacation home brand with vacation rental management brands Belvilla,<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://techcrunch.com/2019/05/01/airbnb-backed-oyo-moves-into-europe-acquires-leisure-from-axel-springer-for-415m/ | title=Airbnb-backed OYO moves into Europe, buys Leisure Group from Axel Springer for $415M | work=[[TechCrunch]] | date=1 May 2019}}</ref> Danland,<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/startups/newsbuzz/oyo-to-acquire-amsterdam-based-vacation-rental-company-leisure-group/articleshow/69129470.cms | title=OYO to acquire Amsterdam based vacation rental company @Leisure Group | work=[[The Economic Times]] | date=2 May 2019}}</ref> and DanCenter<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://techcrunch.com/2019/08/14/oyo-vacation-rental-europe/ | title=Oyo to invest $335M in vacation rental business in Europe push | work=[[TechCrunch]] | date=14 August 2019}}</ref> along with Germany-based Traum-Ferienwohnungen.\n* '''SilverKey''' launched in April 2018, caters to the needs of the corporate travellers undertaking business trips for a short or long duration.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/startups/newsbuzz/oyo-to-scale-up-its-silverkey-hotels-portfolio-to-19-cities-across-india/articleshow/68698845.cms | title=OYO to scale up its SilverKey hotels portfolio to 19 cities across India | work=[[The Economic Times]] | date=3 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/companies/oyo-plans-big-focus-on-serviced-apartments-for-corporate-clients-118041800353_1.html | title=OYO plans big focus on serviced apartments for corporate clients | work=[[Business Standard]] | date=18 April 2018}}</ref>\n* '''Capital O''' are premium hotels located in prime locations and especially curated to deliver OYO's quality-assured experience at an affordable price.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.arabianbusiness.com/travel-hospitality/423960-indias-oyo-launches-capital-o-hotels-in-the-uae | title=India's Oyo launches Capital O hotels in the UAE | work=[[Arabian Business]] | date=16 July 2019}}</ref>\n* '''Palette''' offers the perfectly curated staycation for those in search of an intuitive experience at competitive prices, an upper-end leisure resorts category.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/business/india-business/oyo-forays-into-leisure-segment-with-palette-resorts/articleshow/65607782.cms | title=Oyo forays into leisure segment with Palette Resorts | work=[[The Times of India]] | date=30 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/startups/newsbuzz/oyo-forays-into-upper-end-leisure-resorts-category-launches-palette-resorts/articleshow/65607265.cms | title=OYO forays into upper-end leisure resorts category; launches Palette Resorts | work=[[The Economic Times]] | date=30 August 2018}}</ref>\n* '''Collection O''' is the newest category under OYO's hotel portfolio that caters to the requirements of discerning business travellers.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/nation/current-affairs/130319/oyo-woos-biz-travellers-with-collection-o-ups-investment.html | title=OYO woos biz travellers with Collection O; ups investment | work=[[Deccan Chronicle]] | date=13 March 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.aninews.in/news/business/oyos-collection-o-hotels-reaches-milestone-175-buildings-in-3-months20190713124833/ | title=OYO's Collection O Hotels reaches milestone 175 buildings in 3 months | work=[[Asian News International]] | date=13 July 2019}}</ref>\n* '''OYO LIFE''', targeted at millennials and young professionals in search of fully managed homes on long-term rentals, at affordable prices. This is a PG based model where you can take a room or share it with a friend without any restrictions<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/why-oyo-life-betting-big-co-living-market-india-101514 | title=Why OYO Life is betting big on the co-living market in India | work=[[The News Minute]] | date=9 May 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/startups/newsbuzz/oyo-looks-to-enter-student-housing-and-co-working-to-expand-co-living-segments/articleshow/69172676.cms | title=Oyo looks to enter student housing and co-working, to expand co-living segments | work=[[The Economic Times]] | date=6 May 2019}}</ref>\n*OYO has grouped all its products into a single category, that is OYO Rooms and homes.{{cn|date=March 2020}}\n\n==OYO Partner Engagement==\nIn April 2019, the company announced the launch of OPEN programme, an initiative for its partner hotels to help them reach their business goals. It further Introduced upgraded Co-OYO app for hotel partners to provide complete visibility on all business & customer metrics. <ref>{{Cite news | url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/startups/newsbuzz/oyo-launches-open-programme-for-asset-owners/articleshow/68937688.cms | title=OYO launches OPEN programme for asset owners |  work=[[The Economic Times]] | date=18 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Awards and honours==\n* In 2019 Agarwal was featured in the Bloomberg 50 list as \u2018The Amazingly Ambitious Hotelier\u2019,<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.bloombergquint.com/businessweek/ritesh-agarwal-s-oyo-rooms-is-poised-to-overtake-marriott | title=Ritesh Agarwal, the Amazingly Ambitious Hotelier | work=BloombergQuint | date=4 December 2019}}</ref> the 50 most powerful people in India by India Today and the Tycoons of Tomorrow\u2019 by Forbes India.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.forbesindia.com/lists/tycoons-of-tomorrow/1729/1|title=Tycoons of Tomorrow|website=Forbes India|language=en-US|access-date=10 December 2019}}</ref>\n* His net worth in 2019 was estimated to be approximately $1&nbsp;billion (7000 crore INR) according to IIFL Wealth Hurun India Rich List.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.outlookindia.com/outlookmoney/talking-money/iifl-wealth-hurun-india-rich-list-2019-all-you-need-to-know-3619 | title=IIFL Wealth Hurun India Rich List 2019: All You Need To Know | work=Outlook (Indian magazine) | date=26 September 2019}}</ref>\n* Market Entrant of the Year 2019 (UK-India Awards)<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.hotelowner.co.uk/22072-oyo-hotels-wins-market-entrant-of-the-year-at-uk-india-awards/ | title=OYO Hotels wins 'Market Entrant of the Year' at UK-India Awards | work=Hotel Owner | date=2 July 2019}}</ref>\n* Fast Company's World's Most Innovative Companies for 2019 \u2013 India edition<ref>{{Cite web| url=https://www.fastcompany.com/most-innovative-companies/2019/sectors/india | title=The World's Most Innovative Companies 2019: India Honorees|date=20 September 2019 | access-date=20 September 2019}}</ref>\n* Best Startup \u2013 SATTE Awards 2019<ref>{{Cite news | url=http://www.satteawards.com/winners-2019.html | title=Best Startup \u2013 SATTE Awards 2019 | date=16 January 2019}}</ref>\n* OYO topped the maiden list of LinkedIn's Top Startups in India (2018)<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.moneycontrol.com/news/business/linkedin-says-these-are-the-25-most-attractive-startups-to-work-for-in-india-2961531.html | title=LinkedIn says these are the 25 most attractive startups to work for in India | date=18 September 2018}}</ref>\n* LinkedIn has recognized OYO as one of the top employee attractors 