ss-date=20 September 2019}}</ref>\n* OneDirect Quest CX Award for Best Use of Social Media (2016)<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://inc42.com/buzz/onedirect-quest/ | title=OneDirect organised the Second Edition of Quest \u2013 India's largest Customer Experience Management Summit | work=Inc42 | date=27 April 2016}}</ref>\n* No. 2 in BT Coolest Start-ups Survey 2016<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.businesstoday.in/photos/coolest-start-ups/coolest-start-ups-of-india-2016/1075.html#photo2 | title=Coolest Start-Ups of India 2016 | work=[[Business Today (India)]] | date=27 April 2016}}</ref>\n* Startup of the Year- Express IT Award (2015)<ref>{{Cite web| url=http://expressitawards.financialexpress.com/winner2015/ | title=Winners 2015 \u2013 Express I.T Awards  |date=20 September 2017 | access-date=20 September 2019}}</ref>\n* In March 2020, [[Ivanka Trump]], the senior advisor to President [[Donald Trump]], had lauded an initiative by OYO Hotels to offer free stays to doctors, nurses in the US helping in the fight against the novel coronavirus, describing the gesture as \u201cimpactful acts of benevolence\u201d.<ref>{{cite news |title=Ivanka Trump lauds Indian hotel chain OYO for offering free stays to doctors in US amid COVID19 crisis |url=https://www.moneycontrol.com/news/business/ivanka-trump-lauds-indian-hotel-chain-oyo-for-offering-free-stays-to-doctors-in-us-amid-covid19-crisis-5070191.html |accessdate=26 March 2020 |work=Moneycontrol |date=25 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Controversies==\n===Sharing of customer data with the government===\nIn 2019, OYO rooms plans to implement a digital register mechanism which will allow it to share customer data in real time with the government. This has been described as a threat to privacy.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.indiatoday.in/technology/news/story/oyo-rooms-wants-to-share-digital-record-of-your-check-ins-with-government-1431439-2019-01-15 | title=Oyo Rooms wants to share digital record of your check-ins with government | work=[[India Today]] | date=15 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.indianpeopletimes.com/digital-world/oyorooms-with-new-concept-of-digital-data-sharing-with-government/ | title=Oyorooms with new concept of data sharing with government authorities | work=Indian people times | date=16 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Use of predatory pricing===\nOYO has been accused of using [[predatory pricing]] and not following its own agreements including threatening hotels to unilaterally change some of the clauses or not be paid.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/services/hotels-/-restaurants/budget-hotels-teaming-up-to-take-legal-route-against-oyo/articleshow/66890345.cms | title=Budget hotels teaming up to take legal route against Oyo | first=Anumeha | last=Chaturvedi | work=[[The Economic Times]] | date=1 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Sending of unsolicited emails===\nIn 2018, the company sent mass unsolicited job offer emails targeting senior- and mid-level employees of competitors.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.livemint.com/Industry/ML1hLZR50QT08vsDMPfSzK/Alls-fair-in-talent-war-Oyo-targets-staff-at-rivals.html | title=All's fair in talent war: Oyo targets staff at rivals | last=S.H. | first=Salman | work=[[Mint (newspaper)|Mint]] | date=27 April 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== Downsizing of OYO China ===\nIn March 2020, it was reported that OYO China will downsize and lay off up to 72% of its staff. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mingtiandi.com/real-estate/finance-real-estate/oyo-hotels-said-to-cut-over-72-of-china-staff/|title=Oyo Hotels Said to Cut Over 72% of China Staff|date=14 March 2020|website=Mingtiandi|language=en-US|access-date=19 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Official website}}\n\n{{SoftBank}}\n{{Hospitality_service}}\n\n[[Category:Hotel affiliation groups]]\n[[Category:Hotel chains in India]]\n[[Category:Indian companies established in 2013]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Gurgao